  "issue_title": "Issue bounties cast cancel votes when solver lookup fails (API/rate-limit path)",
  "issue_body": "## Description\n\nWhen GitHub solver lookup fails (for example due to GraphQL/API failure or rate limiting), the issue-bounties flow treats it as \"no solver found\" and casts a cancel vote.  \nThis makes transient API failures policy-indistinguishable from genuine no-solver closures.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Make `check_github_issue_closed` see the issue as closed, but force solver lookup failure (e.g. GraphQL failure/`None` result in `find_solver_from_cross_references` path).\n2. Run `issue_competitions(...)` with an active contract issue.\n3. Observe `vote_cancel_issue(...)` is called with reason `\"Issue closed without identifiable solver\"`.\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nIf solver lookup fails due to API/GraphQL/rate-limit errors, validator should **not** cast a cancel vote.  \nIt should skip voting for that issue and retry on a later round.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nSolver lookup failure is collapsed into `(None, None)`, and forward logic treats `not solver_github_id` as true no-solver, then casts cancel.\n\n## Environment\n\n- OS: Linux\n- Python version: 3.12.3\n- Commit/Version: `test` branch before fix (e.g. `9424da7`)\n\n## Additional Context\n\nImpacted paths:\n- `gittensor/utils/github_api_tools.py` (`find_solver_from_cross_references`, `check_github_issue_closed`)\n- `gittensor/validator/issue_competitions/forward.py`\n\nRoot cause:\n- Solver lookup failures return `(None, None)` and are not explicitly marked as failure state.\n- Forward logic uses falsy solver ID to trigger cancel voting.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-04-20T13:49:24.000Z",
